  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Risk Management Facilitator",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p><p>Ø  To successfully manage the Preparation of Civil Construction Safety Submission (CNSS), Civil Design Safety Submission (CDSS) and Project Safety Review (PSR)</p><p>Ø  Present at LTA’s project Safety committee Meeting (PSCM) for review of CNSS</p><p>Ø  Perform risk analysis, risk monitoring and reporting</p><p>Ø  Preparation and submission of documentations of Civil Design safety, Construction Safety and Project Safety reviews to LTA</p><p>Ø  Conduct presentations and Risk Management meeting with LTA</p><p>Ø  Maintenance of risk registrar</p><p>Ø  Identify risks and ensure all requirements during design & construction stage are addressed with suitable protection and mitigation measures</p><p>Ø  Prepare, maintain and update project Risk Register as project progresses</p><p>Ø  Able to convene and facilitate Design for Safety Review Workshops / Meeting in accordance to GUIDE 1, GUIDE 2 and GUIDE 3; prepare and Maintain Design Risk Registers, Prepare Design Risk Health and Safety documentation to be handed over to Developers.</p><p>Ø  Lead Risk Management team and coordinate Risk Management implementation.</p><p>Ø  Coordinate with QPD and Internal Design team to prepare the documentation for civil design safety\nand CNSS submission to LTA.</p><p>Ø  Prepare and deliver all necessary Method Statement & Risk Assessments for the projects</p><p>Ø  Facilitate the hazard identification and Risk assessments for preparation of safety submission.</p><p>Ø  Liaise with the external RMFs on hazard management</p><p>Ø  Liaise with various government authorities and external agencies to get necessary approval.</p><p>Ø  Evaluate subcontractor's risk assessment, safe work procedures and method statements</p><p>Ø  To coordinate and review all the submissions from subcontractors.</p><p>Ø  Reports directly to Design Manager and supports Design team</p><p>Ø  To coordinate with drafters and ensure all the client's requirement are promptly met.</p><p><u><strong>Requirement:</strong></u></p><p>Ø  Minimum 5 years of geotechnical engineering experience with Degree in Civil Engineering recognized by the PE Board or qualification acceptable to the Commissioner of Building Control as eligible for application as a Resident Engineer or recognized Degree in the relevant field subject to the acceptance of the Engineer, and at least 3\nyears of experience in the design of similar scale and complexity.</p><p>Ø  At least 3 years of experience in design for LTA’s project</p><p>Ø  At least 3 years of experience in design for elevated station and Viaduct project (Optional)</p><p>Ø  A registered PE or Architect with a Practicing Certificate or have 10 years of relevant experience in the design (at least 5 years in design which includes contribution to designs, writing specifications) and the supervision of the construction of structures; and have a degree accepted by PEB or BOA and construction-related degree accepted by SISV and SPM. The DFS professional shall also have:</p><p>Ø  Reasonable exposure in safety and health for construction;</p><p>Ø  Attended the Design for Safety for Professional Course and passed the assessments or equivalent;</p><p>Ø  Experience in design and construction management of transit projects; and</p><p>Ø  Trained in hazard identification and risk assessment methodology.</p>",
